      • UploadEvents

        public void UploadEvents(CalendarSettings settings)
        Uploads users events to the Google Calendar. If the settings object startDateIndex field is properly initialized in the settings.txt file, the events are non-recurring. That means that every event has a start and an end date. If not, the events have a day name information alongside them, so they will be recurring, and repeat themselves every weekend on the same day. They do not have explicit start and end dates.
        Specified by:
        UploadEvents in interface Uploader
        Parameters:
        settings - A CalendarSettings object

      • UploadRecurringEvents
